The course examines the changing relationships between academic study and new configurations of museum display and interpretation. Such topics as the roles of museums in modern cultures, museum education programs and audiences, new technologies, collection management, curatorial work etc.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course brings the academic study of art museums together with museum practice, and emphasizes the international contexts of museums in the modern world.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  During this course the students will:
*	gain the practical knowledge and understanding about the structure, work, collections, catalogue and databases of the museums in Tartu
*	understand current developments in the museum sector and gain a critical awareness of problems and new insights
*	undertake an extended placement to further enhance your practical skills and knowledge
